interfaces.label: FeatureKibanaPrivileges
description: Feature privilege definition

children.label: excludeFromBasePrivileges
description: Whether or not this specific privilege should be excluded from the base privileges.

children.label: requireAllSpaces
description:
Whether or not this privilege should only be granted to `All Spaces *`. Should be used for features that do not
support Spaces. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: disabled
description: Whether or not this privilege should be hidden in the roles UI and disallowed on the API. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: management
description:
If this feature includes management sections, you can specify them here to control visibility of those
pages based on user privileges.

children.label: catalogue
description: If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on user permissions.

children.label: api
description: If your feature includes server-side APIs, you can tag those routes to secure access based on user permissions.

children.label: app
description: If your feature exposes a client-side application (most of them do!), then you can control access to them here.

children.label: alerting
description:
If your feature requires access to specific Alert Types, then specify your access needs here.
Include both Alert Types registered by the feature and external Alert Types such as built-in
Alert Types and Alert Types provided by other features to which you wish to grant access.

children.label: cases
description:
If your feature requires access to specific owners of cases (aka plugins that have created cases), then specify your access needs here. The values here should
be unique identifiers for the owners of cases you want access to.
signature: { all?: readonly string[] | undefined; push?: readonly string[] | undefined; create?: readonly string[] | undefined; read?: readonly string[] | undefined; update?: readonly string[] | undefined; delete?: readonly string[] | undefined; settings?: readonly string[] | undefined; createComment?: readonly string[] | undefined; reopenCase?: readonly string[] | undefined; assign?: readonly string[] | undefined; } | undefined

children.label: savedObject
description: If your feature requires access to specific saved objects, then specify your access needs here.
signature: { all: readonly string[]; read: readonly string[]; }

children.label: ui
description:
A list of UI Capabilities that should be granted to users with this privilege.
These capabilities will automatically be namespaces within your feature id.

children.label: composedOf
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that this privilege is composed of. When
privilege is registered with Elasticsearch, it will be expanded to grant everything that referenced privileges
grant. This property can only be set in the feature configuration overrides.

children.label: replacedBy
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that, when combined, grant equivalent access
if the feature this privilege belongs to becomes deprecated. The extended definition allows separate lists of
privileges to be defined for the default and minimal (excludes any automatically granted sub-feature privileges)
sets. This property can only be set if the feature is marked as deprecated.

interfaces.label: KibanaFeatureConfig
description:
Interface for registering a feature.
Feature registration allows plugins to hide their applications with spaces,
and secure access when configured for security.

children.label: id
description:
Unique identifier for this feature.
This identifier is also used when generating UI Capabilities.

children.label: name
description:
Display name for this feature.
This will be displayed to end-users, so a translatable string is advised for i18n.

children.label: description
description: An optional description that will appear as subtext underneath the feature name

children.label: category
description:
The category for this feature.
This will be used to organize the list of features for display within the
Spaces and Roles management screens.

children.label: order
description: An ordinal used to sort features relative to one another for display.

children.label: excludeFromBasePrivileges
description:
Whether or not this feature should be excluded from the base privileges.
This is primarily helpful when migrating applications with a "legacy" privileges model
to use Kibana privileges. We don't want these features to be considered part of the `all`
or `read` base privileges in a minor release if the user was previously granted access
using an additional reserved role.

children.label: minimumLicense
description:
Optional minimum supported license.
If omitted, all licenses are allowed.
This does not restrict access to your feature based on license.
Its only purpose is to inform the space and roles UIs on which features to display.

children.label: app
description:
An array of app ids that are enabled when this feature is enabled.
Apps specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: management
description:
If this feature includes management sections, you can specify them here to control visibility of those
pages based on the current space.

Items specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: catalogue
description:
If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

Items specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: alerting
description:
If your feature grants access to specific rule types, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.
Include both rule types registered by the feature and external rule types such as built-in
rule types and rule types provided by other features to which you wish to grant access. For each rule type
you can specify the consumers the feature has access to.

children.label: cases
description: If your feature grants access to specific case types, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

children.label: privileges
description: Feature privilege definition.

children.label: subFeatures
description: Optional sub-feature privilege definitions. This can only be specified if `privileges` are are also defined.

children.label: privilegesTooltip
description: Optional message to display on the Role Management screen when configuring permissions for this feature.

children.label: hidden
description:
Indicates whether the feature is available as a standalone feature. The feature can still be
referenced by other features, but it will not be displayed in any feature management UIs. By default, all features
are visible.

children.label: deprecated
description: If defined, the feature is considered deprecated and won't be available to users when configuring roles or Spaces.
signature: Readonly<{ notice: string; replacedBy?: readonly string[] | undefined; }> | undefined

interfaces.label: SubFeatureConfig
description: Configuration for a sub-feature.

children.label: name
description: Display name for this sub-feature

children.label: requireAllSpaces
description:
Whether or not this privilege should only be granted to `All Spaces *`. Should be used for features that do not
support Spaces. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: privilegesTooltip
description: Optional message to display on the Role Management screen when configuring permissions for this feature.

children.label: privilegeGroups
description: Collection of privilege groups

children.label: description
description: An optional description that will appear as subtext underneath the sub-feature name

interfaces.label: SubFeaturePrivilegeConfig
description: Configuration for a sub-feature privilege.

children.label: id
description: Identifier for this privilege. Must be unique across all other privileges within a feature.

children.label: name
description: The display name for this privilege.

children.label: includeIn
description:
Denotes which Primary Feature Privilege this sub-feature privilege should be included in.
`read` is also included in `all` automatically.

children.label: minimumLicense
description:
The minimum supported license level for this sub-feature privilege.
If no license level is supplied, then this privilege will be available for all licences
that are valid for the overall feature.

children.label: replacedBy
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that, when combined, grant equivalent access
if the feature this sub-feature privilege belongs to becomes deprecated. This property can only be set if the
feature is marked as deprecated.

interfaces.label: ElasticsearchFeatureConfig
description:
Interface for registering an Elasticsearch feature.
Feature registration allows plugins to hide their applications based
on configured cluster or index privileges.

children.label: id
description:
Unique identifier for this feature.
This identifier is also used when generating UI Capabilities.

children.label: management
description: Management sections associated with this feature.

children.label: catalogue
description: If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

children.label: privileges
description:
Feature privilege definition. Specify one or more privileges which grant access to this feature.
Users must satisfy all privileges in at least one of the defined sets of privileges in order to be granted access.

interfaces.label: FeatureElasticsearchPrivileges
description: Elasticsearch Feature privilege definition

children.label: requiredClusterPrivileges
description:
A set of Elasticsearch cluster privileges which are required for this feature to be enabled.
See https://www.elastic.co/docs/reference/elasticsearch/security-privileges

children.label: requiredIndexPrivileges
description:
A set of Elasticsearch index privileges which are required for this feature to be enabled, keyed on index name or pattern.
See https://www.elastic.co/docs/reference/elasticsearch/security-privileges#privileges-list-indices

children.label: requiredRoles
description: A set of Elasticsearch roles which are required for this feature to be enabled.
children.removeBy:
8.8.0

This is relied on by the reporting feature, and should be removed once reporting
migrates to using the Kibana Privilege model: https://github.com/elastic/kibana/issues/19914

children.label: ui
description:
A list of UI Capabilities that should be granted to users with this privilege.
These capabilities will automatically be namespaces within your feature id.

interfaces.label: FeatureKibanaPrivileges
description: Feature privilege definition

children.label: excludeFromBasePrivileges
description: Whether or not this specific privilege should be excluded from the base privileges.

children.label: requireAllSpaces
description:
Whether or not this privilege should only be granted to `All Spaces *`. Should be used for features that do not
support Spaces. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: disabled
description: Whether or not this privilege should be hidden in the roles UI and disallowed on the API. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: management
description:
If this feature includes management sections, you can specify them here to control visibility of those
pages based on user privileges.

children.label: catalogue
description: If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on user permissions.

children.label: api
description: If your feature includes server-side APIs, you can tag those routes to secure access based on user permissions.

children.label: app
description: If your feature exposes a client-side application (most of them do!), then you can control access to them here.

children.label: alerting
description:
If your feature requires access to specific Alert Types, then specify your access needs here.
Include both Alert Types registered by the feature and external Alert Types such as built-in
Alert Types and Alert Types provided by other features to which you wish to grant access.

children.label: cases
description:
If your feature requires access to specific owners of cases (aka plugins that have created cases), then specify your access needs here. The values here should
be unique identifiers for the owners of cases you want access to.
signature: { all?: readonly string[] | undefined; push?: readonly string[] | undefined; create?: readonly string[] | undefined; read?: readonly string[] | undefined; update?: readonly string[] | undefined; delete?: readonly string[] | undefined; settings?: readonly string[] | undefined; createComment?: readonly string[] | undefined; reopenCase?: readonly string[] | undefined; assign?: readonly string[] | undefined; } | undefined

children.label: savedObject
description: If your feature requires access to specific saved objects, then specify your access needs here.
signature: { all: readonly string[]; read: readonly string[]; }

children.label: ui
description:
A list of UI Capabilities that should be granted to users with this privilege.
These capabilities will automatically be namespaces within your feature id.

children.label: composedOf
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that this privilege is composed of. When
privilege is registered with Elasticsearch, it will be expanded to grant everything that referenced privileges
grant. This property can only be set in the feature configuration overrides.

children.label: replacedBy
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that, when combined, grant equivalent access
if the feature this privilege belongs to becomes deprecated. The extended definition allows separate lists of
privileges to be defined for the default and minimal (excludes any automatically granted sub-feature privileges)
sets. This property can only be set if the feature is marked as deprecated.

interfaces.label: FeaturesPluginSetup
description: Describes public Features plugin contract returned at the `setup` stage.

children.label: getKibanaFeatures
description:
Calling this function during setup will crash Kibana.
Use start contract instead.

children.label: getElasticsearchFeatures
description:
Calling this function during setup will crash Kibana.
Use start contract instead.

children.label: enableReportingUiCapabilities
description:
In the future, OSS features should register their own subfeature
privileges. This can be done when parts of Reporting are moved to
src/plugins. For now, this method exists for `reporting` to tell
`features` to include Reporting when registering OSS features.

children.label: featurePrivilegeIterator
description:
Utility for iterating through all privileges belonging to a specific feature.
{@see FeaturePrivilegeIterator }

children.label: subFeaturePrivilegeIterator
description:
Utility for iterating through all sub-feature privileges belonging to a specific feature.
{@see SubFeaturePrivilegeIterator }

children.label: getKibanaFeatures
description: Returns all registered Kibana features.

children.label: params
description: Optional parameters to filter features.

interfaces.label: GetKibanaFeaturesParams
description: Describes parameters used to retrieve all Kibana features (for public consumers).

children.label: omitDeprecated
description:
If true, deprecated features will be omitted. For backward compatibility reasons, deprecated features are included
in the result by default.

interfaces.label: KibanaFeatureConfig
description:
Interface for registering a feature.
Feature registration allows plugins to hide their applications with spaces,
and secure access when configured for security.

children.label: id
description:
Unique identifier for this feature.
This identifier is also used when generating UI Capabilities.

children.label: name
description:
Display name for this feature.
This will be displayed to end-users, so a translatable string is advised for i18n.

children.label: description
description: An optional description that will appear as subtext underneath the feature name

children.label: category
description:
The category for this feature.
This will be used to organize the list of features for display within the
Spaces and Roles management screens.

children.label: order
description: An ordinal used to sort features relative to one another for display.

children.label: excludeFromBasePrivileges
description:
Whether or not this feature should be excluded from the base privileges.
This is primarily helpful when migrating applications with a "legacy" privileges model
to use Kibana privileges. We don't want these features to be considered part of the `all`
or `read` base privileges in a minor release if the user was previously granted access
using an additional reserved role.

children.label: minimumLicense
description:
Optional minimum supported license.
If omitted, all licenses are allowed.
This does not restrict access to your feature based on license.
Its only purpose is to inform the space and roles UIs on which features to display.

children.label: app
description:
An array of app ids that are enabled when this feature is enabled.
Apps specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: management
description:
If this feature includes management sections, you can specify them here to control visibility of those
pages based on the current space.

Items specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: catalogue
description:
If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

Items specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: alerting
description:
If your feature grants access to specific rule types, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.
Include both rule types registered by the feature and external rule types such as built-in
rule types and rule types provided by other features to which you wish to grant access. For each rule type
you can specify the consumers the feature has access to.

children.label: cases
description: If your feature grants access to specific case types, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

children.label: privileges
description: Feature privilege definition.

children.label: subFeatures
description: Optional sub-feature privilege definitions. This can only be specified if `privileges` are are also defined.

children.label: privilegesTooltip
description: Optional message to display on the Role Management screen when configuring permissions for this feature.

children.label: hidden
description:
Indicates whether the feature is available as a standalone feature. The feature can still be
referenced by other features, but it will not be displayed in any feature management UIs. By default, all features
are visible.

children.label: deprecated
description: If defined, the feature is considered deprecated and won't be available to users when configuring roles or Spaces.
signature: Readonly<{ notice: string; replacedBy?: readonly string[] | undefined; }> | undefined

description: Utility for iterating through all sub-feature privileges belonging to a specific feature.

children.label: feature
description: the feature whose sub-feature privileges to iterate through.

interfaces.label: ElasticsearchFeatureConfig
description:
Interface for registering an Elasticsearch feature.
Feature registration allows plugins to hide their applications based
on configured cluster or index privileges.

children.label: id
description:
Unique identifier for this feature.
This identifier is also used when generating UI Capabilities.

children.label: management
description: Management sections associated with this feature.

children.label: catalogue
description: If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

children.label: privileges
description:
Feature privilege definition. Specify one or more privileges which grant access to this feature.
Users must satisfy all privileges in at least one of the defined sets of privileges in order to be granted access.

interfaces.label: FeatureElasticsearchPrivileges
description: Elasticsearch Feature privilege definition

children.label: requiredClusterPrivileges
description:
A set of Elasticsearch cluster privileges which are required for this feature to be enabled.
See https://www.elastic.co/docs/reference/elasticsearch/security-privileges

children.label: requiredIndexPrivileges
description:
A set of Elasticsearch index privileges which are required for this feature to be enabled, keyed on index name or pattern.
See https://www.elastic.co/docs/reference/elasticsearch/security-privileges#privileges-list-indices

children.label: requiredRoles
description: A set of Elasticsearch roles which are required for this feature to be enabled.
children.removeBy:
8.8.0

This is relied on by the reporting feature, and should be removed once reporting
migrates to using the Kibana Privilege model: https://github.com/elastic/kibana/issues/19914

children.label: ui
description:
A list of UI Capabilities that should be granted to users with this privilege.
These capabilities will automatically be namespaces within your feature id.

interfaces.label: FeatureKibanaPrivileges
description: Feature privilege definition

children.label: excludeFromBasePrivileges
description: Whether or not this specific privilege should be excluded from the base privileges.

children.label: requireAllSpaces
description:
Whether or not this privilege should only be granted to `All Spaces *`. Should be used for features that do not
support Spaces. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: disabled
description: Whether or not this privilege should be hidden in the roles UI and disallowed on the API. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: management
description:
If this feature includes management sections, you can specify them here to control visibility of those
pages based on user privileges.

children.label: catalogue
description: If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on user permissions.

children.label: api
description: If your feature includes server-side APIs, you can tag those routes to secure access based on user permissions.

children.label: app
description: If your feature exposes a client-side application (most of them do!), then you can control access to them here.

children.label: alerting
description:
If your feature requires access to specific Alert Types, then specify your access needs here.
Include both Alert Types registered by the feature and external Alert Types such as built-in
Alert Types and Alert Types provided by other features to which you wish to grant access.

children.label: cases
description:
If your feature requires access to specific owners of cases (aka plugins that have created cases), then specify your access needs here. The values here should
be unique identifiers for the owners of cases you want access to.
signature: { all?: readonly string[] | undefined; push?: readonly string[] | undefined; create?: readonly string[] | undefined; read?: readonly string[] | undefined; update?: readonly string[] | undefined; delete?: readonly string[] | undefined; settings?: readonly string[] | undefined; createComment?: readonly string[] | undefined; reopenCase?: readonly string[] | undefined; assign?: readonly string[] | undefined; } | undefined

children.label: savedObject
description: If your feature requires access to specific saved objects, then specify your access needs here.
signature: { all: readonly string[]; read: readonly string[]; }

children.label: ui
description:
A list of UI Capabilities that should be granted to users with this privilege.
These capabilities will automatically be namespaces within your feature id.

children.label: composedOf
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that this privilege is composed of. When
privilege is registered with Elasticsearch, it will be expanded to grant everything that referenced privileges
grant. This property can only be set in the feature configuration overrides.

children.label: replacedBy
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that, when combined, grant equivalent access
if the feature this privilege belongs to becomes deprecated. The extended definition allows separate lists of
privileges to be defined for the default and minimal (excludes any automatically granted sub-feature privileges)
sets. This property can only be set if the feature is marked as deprecated.

interfaces.label: FeatureKibanaPrivilegesReference
description: Defines a reference to a set of privileges of a specific feature.

children.label: feature
description: The ID of the feature.

children.label: privileges
description: The set of IDs of feature or sub-feature privileges provided by the feature.

interfaces.label: KibanaFeatureConfig
description:
Interface for registering a feature.
Feature registration allows plugins to hide their applications with spaces,
and secure access when configured for security.

children.label: id
description:
Unique identifier for this feature.
This identifier is also used when generating UI Capabilities.

children.label: name
description:
Display name for this feature.
This will be displayed to end-users, so a translatable string is advised for i18n.

children.label: description
description: An optional description that will appear as subtext underneath the feature name

children.label: category
description:
The category for this feature.
This will be used to organize the list of features for display within the
Spaces and Roles management screens.

children.label: order
description: An ordinal used to sort features relative to one another for display.

children.label: excludeFromBasePrivileges
description:
Whether or not this feature should be excluded from the base privileges.
This is primarily helpful when migrating applications with a "legacy" privileges model
to use Kibana privileges. We don't want these features to be considered part of the `all`
or `read` base privileges in a minor release if the user was previously granted access
using an additional reserved role.

children.label: minimumLicense
description:
Optional minimum supported license.
If omitted, all licenses are allowed.
This does not restrict access to your feature based on license.
Its only purpose is to inform the space and roles UIs on which features to display.

children.label: app
description:
An array of app ids that are enabled when this feature is enabled.
Apps specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: management
description:
If this feature includes management sections, you can specify them here to control visibility of those
pages based on the current space.

Items specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: catalogue
description:
If this feature includes a catalogue entry, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

Items specified here will automatically cascade to the privileges defined below, unless specified differently there.

children.label: alerting
description:
If your feature grants access to specific rule types, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.
Include both rule types registered by the feature and external rule types such as built-in
rule types and rule types provided by other features to which you wish to grant access. For each rule type
you can specify the consumers the feature has access to.

children.label: cases
description: If your feature grants access to specific case types, you can specify them here to control visibility based on the current space.

children.label: privileges
description: Feature privilege definition.

children.label: subFeatures
description: Optional sub-feature privilege definitions. This can only be specified if `privileges` are are also defined.

children.label: privilegesTooltip
description: Optional message to display on the Role Management screen when configuring permissions for this feature.

children.label: hidden
description:
Indicates whether the feature is available as a standalone feature. The feature can still be
referenced by other features, but it will not be displayed in any feature management UIs. By default, all features
are visible.

children.label: deprecated
description: If defined, the feature is considered deprecated and won't be available to users when configuring roles or Spaces.
signature: Readonly<{ notice: string; replacedBy?: readonly string[] | undefined; }> | undefined

interfaces.label: SubFeatureConfig
description: Configuration for a sub-feature.

children.label: name
description: Display name for this sub-feature

children.label: requireAllSpaces
description:
Whether or not this privilege should only be granted to `All Spaces *`. Should be used for features that do not
support Spaces. Defaults to `false`.

children.label: privilegesTooltip
description: Optional message to display on the Role Management screen when configuring permissions for this feature.

children.label: privilegeGroups
description: Collection of privilege groups

children.label: description
description: An optional description that will appear as subtext underneath the sub-feature name

interfaces.label: SubFeaturePrivilegeConfig
description: Configuration for a sub-feature privilege.

children.label: id
description: Identifier for this privilege. Must be unique across all other privileges within a feature.

children.label: name
description: The display name for this privilege.

children.label: includeIn
description:
Denotes which Primary Feature Privilege this sub-feature privilege should be included in.
`read` is also included in `all` automatically.

children.label: minimumLicense
description:
The minimum supported license level for this sub-feature privilege.
If no license level is supplied, then this privilege will be available for all licences
that are valid for the overall feature.

children.label: replacedBy
description:
An optional list of other registered feature or sub-feature privileges that, when combined, grant equivalent access
if the feature this sub-feature privilege belongs to becomes deprecated. This property can only be set if the
feature is marked as deprecated.

interfaces.label: SubFeaturePrivilegeGroupConfig
description: Configuration for a sub-feature privilege group.

children.label: groupType
description:
The type of privilege group.
- `mutually_exclusive`::
    Users will be able to select at most one privilege within this group.
    Privileges must be specified in descending order of permissiveness (e.g. `All`, `Read`, not `Read`, `All)
- `independent`::
    Users will be able to select any combination of privileges within this group.

children.label: privileges
description: The privileges which belong to this group.

misc.label: SubFeaturePrivilegeGroupType
description:
The type of privilege group.
- `mutually_exclusive`::
    Users will be able to select at most one privilege within this group.
    Privileges must be specified in descending order of permissiveness (e.g. `All`, `Read`, not `Read`, `All)
- `independent`::
    Users will be able to select any combination of privileges within this group.
